from ultralytics import YOLO

# Load a pre-trained YOLO model (adjust model type as needed)
model = YOLO("yolo11n.pt")  # n, s, m, l, x versions available

# Perform object detection on an image
results = model.predict(source="圖片1.jpg")  # Can also use video, directory, URL, etc.

# Display the results
results[0].show()  # Show the first image results

from ultralytics import YOLO


model = YOLO("yolo11n.pt")  # n, s, m, l, x versions available

results = model.predict(source="istockphoto-981340772-640_adpp_is.mp4", show=True) # show=True displays the video with detections

WARNING ⚠️ Environment does not support cv2.imshow() or PIL Image.show()



WARNING ⚠️ inference results will accumulate in RAM unless `stream=True` is passed, causing potential out-of-memory
errors for large sources or long-running streams and videos. See https://docs.ultralytics.com/modes/predict/ for help.

Example:
    results = model(source=..., stream=True)  # generator of Results objects
    for r in results:
        boxes = r.boxes  # Boxes object for bbox outputs
        masks = r.masks  # Masks object for segment masks outputs
        probs = r.probs  # Class probabilities for classification outputs

# Get input video properties using OpenCV
cap = cv2.VideoCapture('istockphoto-981340772-640_adpp_is.mp4')
fps = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FPS))
width = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_WIDTH))
height = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_HEIGHT))

# Define the VideoWriter object to save the output video
fourcc = cv2.VideoWriter_fourcc(*"mp4v")  # Codec for .mp4 files
out = cv2.VideoWriter(output_video_path, fourcc, fps, (width, height))

# Process each frame and save the labeled video
for result in results:
    frame = result.plot()  # Overlay labels and boxes on the frame
    out.write(frame)       # Write the labeled frame to the output video file

    # Optionally display a few frames in Colab (not live)
    cv2_imshow(frame)  # Display the frame
    break  # Show only the first frame in Colab to confirm processing

# Release resources
cap.release()
out.release()

print("Labeled video saved as", output_video_path)

# Get input video properties using OpenCV
from ultralytics import YOLO
import cv2
from google.colab.patches import cv2_imshow  # For displaying frames in Colab

# Load the YOLO model
model = YOLO("yolo11m.pt")  # Replace with your specific model file

# Path to the input video
input_video_path = "istockphoto-981340772-640_adpp_is.mp4"

# Output video file path
output_video_path = "labeled_cars.mp4"

# Predict on the video
results = model.predict(source=input_video_path, stream=True)  # stream=True processes frame by frame

# Get input video properties using OpenCV
cap = cv2.VideoCapture(input_video_path)
fps = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FPS))
width = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_WIDTH))
height = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_HEIGHT))

# Define the VideoWriter object to save the output video
fourcc = cv2.VideoWriter_fourcc(*"mp4v")  # Codec for .mp4 files
out = cv2.VideoWriter(output_video_path, fourcc, fps, (width, height))

# Process each frame and save the labeled video
for result in results:
    frame = result.plot()  # Overlay labels and boxes on the frame
    out.write(frame)       # Write the labeled frame to the output video file

# Release resources
cap.release()
out.release()

print("Labeled video saved as", output_video_path)

# Get input video properties using OpenCV
from ultralytics import YOLO
import cv2
from google.colab.patches import cv2_imshow  # For displaying frames in Colab

# Load the YOLO model
model = YOLO("yolo11m-seg.pt")  # Replace with your specific model file

# Path to the input video
input_video_path = "dog.mp4"

# Output video file path
output_video_path = "Segmented_dog_m.mp4"

# Predict on the video
results = model.predict(source=input_video_path, stream=True)  # stream=True processes frame by frame

# Get input video properties using OpenCV
cap = cv2.VideoCapture(input_video_path)
fps = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FPS))
width = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_WIDTH))
height = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_HEIGHT))

# Define the VideoWriter object to save the output video
fourcc = cv2.VideoWriter_fourcc(*"mp4v")  # Codec for .mp4 files
out = cv2.VideoWriter(output_video_path, fourcc, fps, (width, height))

# Process each frame and save the labeled video
for result in results:
    frame = result.plot()  # Overlay labels and boxes on the frame
    out.write(frame)       # Write the labeled frame to the output video file

# Release resources
cap.release()
out.release()

# Get input video properties using OpenCV
from ultralytics import YOLO
import cv2
from google.colab.patches import cv2_imshow  # For displaying frames in Colab

# Load the YOLO model
model = YOLO("yolo11m-pose.pt")  # Replace with your specific model file

# Path to the input video
input_video_path = "baseball.mp4"

# Output video file path
output_video_path = "Posed_baseball_m.mp4"

# Predict on the video
results = model.predict(source=input_video_path, stream=True)  # stream=True processes frame by frame

# Get input video properties using OpenCV
cap = cv2.VideoCapture(input_video_path)
fps = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FPS))
width = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_WIDTH))
height = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_HEIGHT))

# Define the VideoWriter object to save the output video
fourcc = cv2.VideoWriter_fourcc(*"mp4v")  # Codec for .mp4 files
out = cv2.VideoWriter(output_video_path, fourcc, fps, (width, height))

# Process each frame and save the labeled video
for result in results:
    frame = result.plot()  # Overlay labels and boxes on the frame
    out.write(frame)       # Write the labeled frame to the output video file

# Release resources
cap.release()
out.release()

print("Labeled video saved as", output_video_path)

# Get input video properties using OpenCV
from ultralytics import YOLO
import cv2
from google.colab.patches import cv2_imshow  # For displaying frames in Colab

# Load the YOLO model
model = YOLO("yolo11s-obb.pt")  # Replace with your specific model file

# Path to the input video
input_video_path = "city_view.mp4"

# Output video file path
output_video_path = "obb_city_view_s.mp4"

# Predict on the video
results = model.predict(source=input_video_path, stream=True)  # stream=True processes frame by frame

# Get input video properties using OpenCV
cap = cv2.VideoCapture(input_video_path)
fps = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FPS))
width = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_WIDTH))
height = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_HEIGHT))

# Define the VideoWriter object to save the output video
fourcc = cv2.VideoWriter_fourcc(*"mp4v")  # Codec for .mp4 files
out = cv2.VideoWriter(output_video_path, fourcc, fps, (width, height))

# Process each frame and save the labeled video
for result in results:
    frame = result.plot()  # Overlay labels and boxes on the frame
    out.write(frame)       # Write the labeled frame to the output video file

# Release resources
cap.release()
out.release()

print("Labeled video saved as", output_video_path)
